{meta: title Fancy Satin Pillows}
{meta: artist Wanda Jackson}
{meta: composer Jerry Crutchfield and Dee Moeller}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Fancy satin pillows that you bought
[D7]For me to place beneath my head
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I must admit they're very nice
[G]But I would rather have your arms instead
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
To have you here beside me just feel your warmth
[C]So very close is [G]what  I  [D7]need
[G]More than all the fancy satin [D7]pillows
[G]You could ever buy for me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[D7]Still I thank you for the fancy satin pillows
[G]I don't mean to be unkind
[A7]But I can't use 'em both
[D7]And I thought sharing them was what you had in mind
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[G]In the stillness of the night
[C]To have your arms reach [G]out and pull me close [D7]so ten-der-ly
[G]Means more than all the fancy satin [D7]pillows
[G]You could ever buy for me
{end_of_verse}

